Patch Set 1:

It looks from LU-18214 that performance-sanity.sh test_5c is able to reproduce a problem in this code when run on multiple clients in parallel:

 test_5c() {
	touch $DIR/$tfile
	for ((i=0; i < 20001; i++)) {
		echo "R$((i * 10)), 5"
		(( $i == 20000 )) && echo "W0,99999999" && echo "T0" && continue
	} | flocks_test 6 $DIR/$tfile
	rm -r $DIR/$tfile
 }
 run_test 5c "merge 20k flocks"

It would be useful to modify this test case so that the test runs on all available clients, so that it can be run with clientcount=4 and allow a higher number of iterations than 20000 with e.g. "env=TEST5c_COUNT=100000" or "env=SLOW=yes".
